---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { pastExams } from '../../data/resources';
import { materialHref } from '../../lib/materials';
---

<BaseLayout title="Past Exams | Economic Policy Study Site">
  <section class="page-intro">
    <p class="eyebrow">Exam archive</p>
    <h1>Past Exams</h1>
    <p>
      Past exams should be used in layers: first to identify recurring topic families, then under time pressure,
      then again after feedback to repair weak spots.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="split-grid section">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>What the recent exams test</h2>
      <p>
        The sampled 2024 paper includes forward guidance, MPC distribution, optimal monetary policy, the slope of
        the Phillips curve, and Ricardian equivalence. That mix is a good reminder that the final exam rewards both
        formal reasoning and broad policy understanding.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>How to use the archive</h2>
      <ul class="bullet-list">
        <li>Do one exam open-notes first to learn the terrain.</li>
        <li>Do later attempts timed and in full length.</li>
        <li>Compare your structure to the official solutions where they exist.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="resource-grid section">
    {pastExams.map((exam) => (
      <article class="card resource-card">
        <p class="eyebrow">{exam.year}</p>
        <h2>Final exam {exam.year}</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <a href={materialHref(exam.exam)} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
              Open exam PDF
            </a>
          </li>
          {exam.solution ? (
            <li>
              <a href={materialHref(exam.solution)} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
                Open solution PDF
              </a>
            </li>
          ) : (
            <li>No official solution currently available in the local material set.</li>
          )}
        </ul>
      </article>
    ))}
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

